Vision of School

At P.S. 102 Explorers our vision is to cultivate a nurturing inclusive learning community where every student's unique cultural and linguistic background is embraced and celebrated. Where each student is empowered to thrive academically, socially, and emotionally by cultivating confident, compassionate, socially conscious scholars who will make a difference in their communities and use their leadership skills to promote equity and social justice. 


Mission Statement

Our mission is to provide an enriching and equitable education that fosters social, emotional, and academic development by providing ample opportunities that increase confidence in their abilities, creativity, and critical thinking skills. We believe that every child deserves differentiated, highly engaging, and rigorous instruction geared toward individual learning styles that are culturally and linguistically responsive and representative of our school community.  All scholars will be intellectually engaged through well-designed learning tasks and activities that promote opportunities for JOY, student agency, and empowerment.
